article.description: — Damien Forrest scored 20 points as North Alabama beat Alabama State 71-63 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Forrest's 20 lead North Alabama past Alabama State 71-63
article.linkText: Forrest's 20 lead North Alabama past Alabama State 71-63
article.story: FLORENCE, Ala. -- — Damien Forrest scored 20 points as North Alabama beat Alabama State 71-63 on Wednesday night. Forrest had 11 rebounds for the Lions (6-4). Dallas Howell added 11 points while going 4 of 9 (3 for 7 from distance), and he also had seven rebounds. Will Soucie went 4 of 6 from the field to finish with 10 points. Isaiah Range led the way for the Hornets (1-8) with 27 points. Antonio Madlock added 10 points, seven rebounds and five assists for Alabama State. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
